label: Age Uncertainty
rdfs_comment: The assessed temporal uncertainty in the maximum or minimum age estimates, or overall uncertainty for both.

label: Age Uncertainty In Years
rdfs_comment: The temporal uncertainty of the maximumAge and minimumAge, in years.

label: Age Uncertainty Method
rdfs_comment: The method used to generate reported uncertainty calculations.

label: Chronomatric Age
rdfs_comment: The age of a specimen or related materials that is generated from a dating assay.

label: Chronometric Age ID
rdfs_comment: An identifier for the set of information associated with a ChronometricAge. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

label: Chronometric Age Protocol
rdfs_comment: A description of or reference to the methods used to determine the ChronometricAge.

label: Chronometric Age References
rdfs_comment: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with the ChronometricAge.

label: Chronometric Age Remarks
rdfs_comment: Notes or comments about the ChronometricAge.

label: Chronometric Age Uncertainty In Years
rdfs_comment: The temporal uncertainty of the maximumChronometricAge and minimumChronometicAge, in years.

label: Chronometric Age Uncertainty Method
rdfs_comment: The method used to generate the reported uncertainty calculations.

label: Chronometric Date
rdfs_comment: The age of a specimen or related materials that is generated from a dating assay.

label: Chronometric Date ID
rdfs_comment: An identifier for the set of information associated with a ChronometricDate. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.
dcterms_description: GUID reference to the combination of information for one ChronometricDate.

label: Chronometric Date Protocol
rdfs_comment: A description or reference to the methods used to determine the ChronometricDate.

label: Chronometric Date References
rdfs_comment: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with the ChronometricDate.

label: Chronometric Date Remarks
rdfs_comment: Notes or comments about the ChronometricDate.

label: Material Dated
rdfs_comment: A description of the material on which the chronometricAgeProtocol was actually performed, if known.

label: Material Dated ID
rdfs_comment: An identifier for the material on which the chronometricAgeProtocol was performed, if applicable.

label: Maximum Age
rdfs_comment: Upper limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method.

label: Maximum Age Reference System
rdfs_comment: The reference system associated with the maximumAge. For example, BC.

label: Maximum Age Units
rdfs_comment: The units associated with the maximumAge.

label: Maximum Chronometric Age
rdfs_comment: Upper limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method. The expected unit for this field is years. This field, if populated, must have an associated maximumChronometricAgeReferenceSystem.

label: Maximum Chronometric Age ReferenceSystem
rdfs_comment: The reference system associated with the maximumChronometricAge.

label: Minimum Age
rdfs_comment: Lower limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method.

label: Minimum Age Reference System
rdfs_comment: The reference system associated with the minimumAge. For example, AD.

label: Minimum Age Units
rdfs_comment: The units associated with the minimumAge.

label: Minimum Chronometric Age
rdfs_comment: Lower limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method. The expected unit for this field is years. This field, if populated, must have an associated maximumChronometricAgeReferenceSystem.

label: Minimum Chronometric Age Reference System
rdfs_comment: The reference system associated with the minimumChronometricAge.

label: Reported Age
rdfs_comment: The unconverted output of a dating protocol. For example, the conventional radiocarbon age.

label: Reported Age Conversion Protocol
rdfs_comment: The method used for converting the reportedAge into a chronometric date, as captured in the maximumAge, maximumAgeUnits, minimumAge, and minimumAgeUnits fields. For example, calibration of conventional radiocarbon age.

label: Verbatim Chronometric Age
rdfs_comment: The verbatim age for a specimen, whether reported by a dating assay, associated references, or legacy information. For example, this could be the conventional radiocarbon age as given in an AMS dating report. This could also be simply what is reported as the age of a specimen in legacy collections data.

label: Verbatim Chronometric Age Conversion Protocol
rdfs_comment: The method used for converting the verbatimChronometricAge into a chronometric age in years, as captured in the maximumChronometricAge, maximumChronometricAgeReferenceSystem, minimumChronometricAge, and minimumChronometricAgeReferenceSystem fields. For example, calibration of conventional radiocarbon age or the currently accepted age range of a cultural or geological period.
